# ArLibs Future Extensions

This document outlines planned future extensions and modules for the ArLibs plugin framework.

## Configuration Framework

A flexible configuration system is planned that will:
- Support YAML format
- Provide automatic type conversion
- Include validation capabilities
- Support hot reloading

Planned location: `dev.arteam.arlibs.config`

## Command Framework

A comprehensive command framework that will:
- Simplify command registration
- Support sub-commands and command hierarchies
- Provide automatic argument parsing and validation
- Include permission handling
- Support tab completion

Planned location: `dev.arteam.arlibs.commands`

## GUI Framework

An intuitive GUI framework for creating inventory-based interfaces:
- Fluent API for creating menus
- Support for pagination
- Animation capabilities
- Event handling for clicks and other interactions

Planned location: `dev.arteam.arlibs.gui`

## Database Framework

A database abstraction layer supporting:
- Multiple database types (MySQL, SQLite, MongoDB)
- Connection pooling
- ORM-like functionality
- Migration support
- Caching capabilities

Planned location: `dev.arteam.arlibs.database`

## Messaging Framework

A messaging system for inter-plugin and cross-server communication:
- Support for plugin messaging channels
- Redis pub/sub integration
- Message serialization/deserialization
- Event-based message handling

Planned location: `dev.arteam.arlibs.messaging`

## Particle Effects Framework

A framework for creating and managing particle effects:
- Predefined effect patterns
- Custom effect creation
- Animation capabilities
- Performance optimization

Planned location: `dev.arteam.arlibs.particles`

## Hologram API

A simple API for creating and managing holograms:
- Text formatting support
- Dynamic content updates
- Visibility control
- Animation support

Planned location: `dev.arteam.arlibs.holograms`



